# RevHire Team: Detailed Role & Technical Guide

This guide explains exactly what each team member is responsible for, which files they will work on, and how their part of the project functions in simple terms.

---

## 1. Role: The Identity & Profile Architect
**Simplified Goal**: You are the "Door-Keeper" and "Identity Manager." You handle who can enter the site and how their professional background is saved.

### 🔑 What You Own
- **User Identity**: Handling registration (signing up) and login.
- **Access Control**: Making sure an Employer sees an Employer dashboard and a Job Seeker sees a Job Seeker dashboard.
- **Professional Resume Data**: The "extra" details like Education, Skills, and Projects that people add to their profiles.

### 📂 Key Files & Locations
- **Models**: `revhire/src/main/java/com/revhire/model/{User, Company, Education, Skill, Project, Certification, PasswordResetToken}.java`
- **Controllers**: `revhire/src/main/java/com/revhire/controller/{AuthController, ProfileController}.java`
- **Services**: `revhire/src/main/java/com/revhire/service/{UserService, CompanyService}.java`
- **Templates (UI)**: `revhire/src/main/resources/templates/{auth, profile}/` (All files inside these folders).

### 🛠️ How It Works
When a user registers, your code in `UserService` encrypts their password and saves them to the `UserRepository`. When they log in, Spring Security (which you configure) checks if they are "JOBSEEKER" or "EMPLOYER" and sends them to the right page. Your `ProfileController` allows them to "Add Education" or "Edit Skills," saving each piece of data to your specific tables in the database.

---

## 2. Role: The Core Market Specialist
**Simplified Goal**: You are the "Job-Board Expert." You make sure jobs can be posted, found easily, and recommended to the right people.

### 🔑 What You Own
- **Job Postings**: The entire process of an Employer creating, editing, closing, or deleting a job.
- **Advanced Search**: The powerful filters that let users find jobs by location, pay, or type.
- **Recommendation Engine**: The smart logic that tells a user, "Hey, this job matches your skills!"

### 📂 Key Files & Locations
- **Models**: `revhire/src/main/java/com/revhire/model/{Job, SavedJob}.java`
- **Controllers**: `revhire/src/main/java/com/revhire/controller/{JobController, SavedJobController, HomeController}.java`
- **Services**: [revhire/src/main/java/com/revhire/service/JobService.java](file:///c:/Users/shaik/OneDrive/Documents/Tech/revhire-final/revhire/src/main/java/com/revhire/service/JobService.java)
- **Templates (UI)**: `revhire/src/main/resources/templates/{jobs, saved-jobs}/` and [index.html](file:///c:/Users/shaik/OneDrive/Documents/Tech/revhire-final/revhire/src/main/resources/templates/index.html).

### 🛠️ How It Works
When an Employer creates a job, your [JobController](file:///c:/Users/shaik/OneDrive/Documents/Tech/revhire-final/revhire/src/main/java/com/revhire/controller/JobController.java#25-398) receives the data and uses [JobService](file:///c:/Users/shaik/OneDrive/Documents/Tech/revhire-final/revhire/src/main/java/com/revhire/service/JobService.java#14-174) to save it as "ACTIVE." Your search logic in `JobRepository` uses special code (JPQL) to filter through the database. Most importantly, your "Recommendation" logic looks at a user's `preferredRoles` and `skills` (from Member 1's work) and finds jobs where the `requirements` match those keywords.

---

## 3. Role: The Workflow & Pipeline Engineer
**Simplified Goal**: You are the "Action Specialist." You manage the actual process of someone applying for a job and getting hired.

### 🔑 What You Own
- **Application Submission**: The "Apply Now" button and the data it sends.
- **Resume Hub**: Handling PDF uploads, making sure files aren't too big, and allowing employers to download them.
- **Hiring Pipeline**: The "Status" of an application (Applied → Shortlisted → Rejected).

### 📂 Key Files & Locations
- **Models**: `revhire/src/main/java/com/revhire/model/{Application, Resume}.java`
- **Controllers**: `revhire/src/main/java/com/revhire/controller/{ApplicationController, ResumeController}.java`
- **Services**: `revhire/src/main/java/com/revhire/service/{ApplicationService, ResumeService, FileStorageService}.java`
- **Templates (UI)**: `revhire/src/main/resources/templates/{applications, resume}/`.

### 🛠️ How It Works
When a seeker clicks "Apply," your `ApplicationController` takes their chosen `Resume` and links it to the [Job](file:///c:/Users/shaik/OneDrive/Documents/Tech/revhire-final/revhire/src/main/java/com/revhire/controller/JobController.java#341-351). Your `ResumeService` and `FileStorageService` work together to save the physical PDF file safely on the server. When an employer wants to interview someone, your code updates the [Application](file:///c:/Users/shaik/OneDrive/Documents/Tech/revhire-final/revhire/src/main/java/com/revhire/service/ApplicationService.java#15-137) status to "SHORTLISTED." This is your "Pipeline" logic.

---

## 4. Role: The Engagement & Intelligence Lead
**Simplified Goal**: You are the "Information Hub." You make sure everyone knows what's happening and show them the data.

### 🔑 What You Own
- **Notification System**: Sending real-time alerts in the app and emails through Gmail.
- **Employer/Seeker Dashboards**: The "Home Base" where users see their stats (e.g., "5 people applied to your job").
- **Platform Analytics**: Calculating counts, views, and success rates.

### 📂 Key Files & Locations
- **Models**: [revhire/src/main/java/com/revhire/model/Notification.java](file:///c:/Users/shaik/OneDrive/Documents/Tech/revhire-final/revhire/src/main/java/com/revhire/model/Notification.java)
- **Controllers**: `revhire/src/main/java/com/revhire/controller/{NotificationController, EmployerDashboardController}.java`
- **Services**: `revhire/src/main/java/com/revhire/service/{NotificationService, EmailService}.java`
- **Templates (UI)**: `revhire/src/main/resources/templates/{notifications, employer/dashboard.html, jobseeker/dashboard.html}`.

### 🛠️ How It Works
Your code is like the "Messenger." When Member 3's code changes an application status, your `NotificationService` is called to send an alert. Your `EmailService` connects to a Gmail account to send the official message. On the Dashboard, your controllers run calculations like `applicationRepository.countByJobId()` to show the employer exactly how much activity is happening on their job posts.
